title: Damaged and Destroyed Villages Darfur Sudan 2010
name: Damaged and Destroyed Villages Darfur Sudan 2010
description:
The "Darfur Damaged and Destroyed Villages" dataset describes the condition of villages in the Darfur region of Sudan that the U.S. Government has confirmed as either "damaged" or "destroyed" between the time period February 2003 to December 2010. Additionally, villages the are confirmed to have "No Damage" are also reported. 

Using the "Darfur Damaged and Destroyed Villages" dataset responsibly

Monitoring the status of villages in Darfur, Sudan is an ongoing process.  After information on the level of damage of villages is collected and confirmed, that information goes into a data table in which entire villages are categorized as not damaged, damaged, or destroyed.  This categorization process is not an exact science, but the methodology employed is a conservative one; the database only includes records of damage and destruction about which there is a high degree of confidence. All estimates about the number of destroyed structures and total structures are approximate. Wherever possible, the year or year range of damage is included in the database field associated with a particular village, though the database does not contain precise dates of damage or destruction. On occasion the "YR_ATTACK" field will include a date range of two different years, for example "2003/2004". This indicates the date range in which the attack was confirmed, and should not be interpreted that there were multiple attacks. 

HIU Modifications

The Humanitarian Information Unit (HIU) of the U.S. Department of State has reformatted the original dataset, in an attempt to increase its usability for quantitative analysis. The original "Structures" data field was parsed into three seperate fields: "Aprox_Str1", "Aprox_Str2", and "Sec_Town". All efforts were made to ensure these data fields matched the original, but if a difference is found, please defer to the original "Structures" field.
